# module function

Renders a complete function implementation contract. The most critical line is the Logic Flow instruction: "step-by-step without skipping any code validations" — this prevents the model from collapsing multi-step sequences. The Errors section now also mandates one regression test per declared error, closing the gap between declared error handling and verified error handling.

# entity SubBlock

The compiler splits the body on `## ` prefixed lines to extract these before rendering.

- kind: 'arg' | 'return' | 'error' | 'flow'
- label: string | undefined — the signature on the sub-header line only (e.g. `cart: &#123;ShoppingCart&#125;`, `ShoppingCart`, `ExpiredCouponError`) — description is not included here
- content: string — the body text on the line(s) following the sub-header, trimmed, until the next `## ` sub-header or end of block

# entity Output

```markdown
### FUNCTION CONTRACT: {{name}}

Implement the {{name}} function according to the binding contract below. Every parameter, the return type, each error condition, and every step of the logic flow are mandatory — do not skip, reorder, rename, or approximate any of them.

#### Parameters

{{args}}

#### Returns

{{return}}

#### Errors

Throw these exact error types under the described conditions only. Do not substitute, wrap, or rename them. For every error listed here, emit at least one regression test that fails without the guard and passes with it — a declared error with no corresponding test is an incomplete implementation:

{{errors}}

#### Logic Flow

Implement the following logical sequence step-by-step without skipping any code validations:

{{flow}}
```

# rule

- name is required and must be camelCase. A missing function name is a PARSE_ERROR.
- A function block with no `## flow` sub-block is a PARSE_ERROR — the logic sequence is mandatory.
- Sub-header syntax: the signature (`name: type`, `type`, or `Type`) is on the `## ` header line; the description is the body text on the following line(s). The compiler reads the header line for the label and subsequent lines for content — they are never on the same line.
- {{args}} expands to one list item per `## arg` sub-block: `- **\`{{label}}\`** — {{content}}`
- {{return}} expands to the `## return` label and content: `` `{{label}}` — {{content}} ``. When no return sub-block is present, renders as `void`.
- {{errors}} expands to one list item per `## error` sub-block: `- **\`{{label}}\`** — {{content}}`. When no error sub-blocks are present, the Errors section and its header are omitted entirely.
- {{flow}} expands to the `## flow` content verbatim, preserving the developer's original numbered list.
- Single-brace variable references in all labels and content are resolved against the reads map before sub-block extraction.
